job_description:
The role is part of the Financial Risk (FR) department who sets and controls the financial risk strategy across the bank by safeguarding ING’s financial health. The department provides strategic guidance on financial risks (in trading and banking books and related to the ING balance sheet), safeguards regulatory compliance, and is the model owner for the banking and trading risk models. FR is also the global functional risk manager for Group Treasury activities.
In the Financial Risk organization, the Banking Risk Management department focuses on managing risks related to the ING Group banking activities in all business lines. Interest Rate risks, Funding & Liquidity risks, Treasury risks and Customer Behaviour risks are the main risk categories. The Customer Behavioural Risk team is responsible for:
Global functional responsibility for oversight of behavioural modelling in the Banking Books including replication towards the Global Treasury function.
Responsible for developing and execution of the global model lifecycle management requirements for customer behavioural risk models.
The Customer Behavioural Risk team is the owner of behavioural risk and replication models used for measuring and managing interest rate and liquidity risks in commercial books such as for mortgage prepayments and savings modelling and their replication. As such, the team is responsible for the functional steering and oversight of customer behaviour risk and replication models of ING locations worldwide.
Within the team, you work in a pleasant and open atmosphere together with very professional colleagues who continually challenge each other intellectually to get the best out of themselves. You get all the space and responsibility to maximize your personal qualities. Working within Financial Risk at ING Bank means working in a highly dynamic international corporate environment where you work together at all levels and with many departments.
Main activities of the team include:
Model lifecycle management of Assets and Liability customer behavioural risk and replication models;
Global functional steering of customer behavioural risk and replication models;
Maintain close relationships with the model stakeholders worldwide.
Performing periodic asset and liability reviews;
Execute financial risk analysis and assessments;
Advice Senior Management and Committees;
Enhance the ALM modelling landscape;
Review of Minimum Standards and Governance;
Monitoring alignment to Financial Risk and modelling standards;
Who are we looking for?
We are looking for a colleague with a quantitative background with an excellent understanding of different types of market risks (interest rate, liquidity and FX risks).
You understand the complexities of a banking group with global operations and have a good understanding of recent regulatory changes and requirements.
You are curious, you are open to new developments and you know how to master your new material quickly. Moreover, you as a person are able to respond well to the wishes and needs of others as an expert advisor.
You are a pragmatic problem solver, who can support the model lifecycle management of Assets and Liability customer behavioural risk and replication models in a dynamic environment.
You are a team player who will add value to the Financial Risk organization within a dynamic environment. You will ensure that the activities you are responsible for will be performed to an exceptional standard.
You possess an excellent command of English, being able to demonstrate negotiation, presentation and writing skills.
You are able to deal with cultural differences, conflicting interests, complex and unforeseen challenges, as well as to constructively cooperate with your peers in building a sustainable, effective and efficient working environment.
Your profile & skills
A completed academic education, preferably in economics, econometrics, or a quantitative specialization or comparable training.
Relevant work experience (min. 5 years) within the financial sector preferably within the banking sector.
Extensive knowledge in the field of Asset and Liability Management and new regulatory developments.
Sound knowledge of risk management and financial products.
Excellent in English, both verbal and writing.
Furthermore, you adhere to the ING values and it is evident to you that your behavior is fully aligned with these values. You are also prepared to take the Banker's Oath.
What we offer
A job from 36 to 40 hours and a unique offer that fits in with the times of today. We take into account your home situation and your ambitions and help you to balance work and private life. Discover yourself our employment conditions.;
A salary tailored to your qualities and experience;
Flexible working hours and the possibility to work at home;
Reimbursement for travel expenses;
24 vacation days with a 36-hour working week. If you work 40 hours a week, you will receive 27 vacation days;
Pension scheme;
13th month salary;•Individual Savings Contribution (BIS), 3.5% of your gross annual salary;
8% Holiday payment;
Personal growth and challenging work with endless possibilities to realize your ambitions;
An informal working environment with innovative colleagues who strive for the very best.
About us
With 57,000 employees and operations in approximately 40 countries, there is no shortage of opportunities for people with initiative who want to help people take a step ahead in life and in business. Do you want to work at the cutting edge of what’s possible and at the same time ensure you work with integrity and hold the customer’s interests at heart? Do you want to be surrounded by progressive, inspiring, diverse and supportive colleagues? Then there is no better place to invest your talents than at ING. Join us. Apply today.

Your work environment
Financial Markets (FM) is the Bank’s gateway to the professional markets around the world. Our primary function is to service the needs of ING’s clients with products, services and guidance. FM aims to be a significant player in our market leader and challenger markets, with an additional presence in all the major international markets and specialist expertise in selected emerging markets and products.
Your role
The FMGT Tribe is the change delivery department of Financial Markets (FM) and Group Treasury (GT) that has as purpose to realize our clients’ dreams by connecting them to global markets, providing financial solutions, and delivering long lasting value.
We are looking for an ambitious and pragmatic team player to strengthen our team of customer journey experts with focus support of the Tribe Management team.
As a Customer Journey Expert (CJE):
You will combine market and system knowledge, product management, and business expertise to take a leading role in successfully delivering change initiatives.
You will be the interfacing function between various stakeholders (trading, sales, Ops, IT, markets, and software vendor partners) to understand the challenges and identify how technology and process can be used to solve them.
You will represent the voice of the business to the squads.
Your key responsibilities
Support efficient change by providing impactful analysis on cross domain, end-to-end, complex environments;
As partner of the squads, maximizes business value by providing clear and developer-ready content for user stories (what is needed, for whom and why) in the squad backlog in AZURE and facilitate alignment of the delivery teams (how) with the businesses/user groups to ensure a strong focus on timely & good quality delivery;
Translate and explain the “What”, give insides into the “Why” so that the IT engineers can determine the appropriate “How”;
Makes sure that the SCOPAFIJTH element of the change delivery are covered and taken care of;
Structure, simplify and solve issues on processes and systems;
Participate/Lead end to end refinement and solution design sessions;
Provide process design and visualisation;
Works independently and ensures that implications of decisions are thought through and get addressed;
Be able to have a good end-to-end vision and manage complexity;
Leads, guides, and inspires others in specific areas and manages the preparations and commitments regarding deliverables;
Establishes and maintains strong (sustainable) relationships with key stakeholders, focused on a clear understanding of their challenges and opportunities. Also, to identify business opportunities to drive revenue and improve product offerings;
Trains and coaches involved parties, ensuring understanding, adoption, and proper implementation of proposed solution(s);
Accumulates and collects knowledge, keeps it up to date and makes it accessible for re-use. Takes initiatives for sharing knowledge.
Who are we looking for?
A colleague with a talent for taking it on and making it happen, enthusiasm for helping others to be successful and a knack for always being a step ahead. In other words, you strive to bring fresh ideas to life and embrace challenges in a fast changing and complex environment. You are a naturally collaborative person who listens and invests in others to achieve common goals. You love to challenge the status quo and are eager to propose creative solutions to problems.
We hire smart people like you for your potential. Our biggest expectation is that you’ll stay curious. Keep learning. Take on responsibility. In return, we’ll back you to develop into an even more awesome version of yourself.
As Customer Journey Expert you will also need:
Completed a bachelor’s degree;
2+ years background in Financial Markets and/or Treasury;
Working in Agile/Scrum is a plus;
Have good analytical skills and be able to analyze large data sets;
You have a basic understanding of statistics and econometrics;
Good communication skills (in English), communication and presentation skills (telling – selling) across different skill and seniority levels;
You are flexible and you easily adapt to a changing environment;
You enjoy working in a diverse and multi-cultural environment, you trust others and can be trusted;
You strive to bring fresh ideas to life and embrace challenges in a fast changing and complex environment.
Rewards & benefits
We want to make sure that it’s possible for you to strike the right balance between your career and your private life. You can find out more about our employment conditions here.
The benefits of working with us at ING include:
A salary tailored to your qualities and experience
A 40-hour working week
An informal working environment with innovative colleagues
Work Agile, so new ideas come to life faster
24-27 vacation days depending on contract
Pension scheme
13th month salary
Individual Savings Contribution (BIS), 3.5% of your gross annual salary
